# Specification: Core Application - UI & Styling Rules
- **ID:** `spec.md.app_styling`
- **Version:** 1.0
- **Date:** October 9, 2025
- **Author:** Gemini, Project Architect

## 1.0 Document Purpose
This document serves as the single source of truth for the styling, UI patterns, and user experience rules for all authenticated (in-app) pages of the Disagreement.AI MVP. Its purpose is to ensure a consistent, calm, and trustworthy user experience, distinct from the public-facing marketing site.

## 2.0 Global In-App Design Rules

### 2.1 Color Palette
- [cite_start]**Primary Blue:** `#2667FF` (Used for primary user actions, user's own chat messages, and highlights) [cite: 44, 168]
- [cite_start]**Neutral - Dark Text:** `#1E293B` (For headlines and primary text) [cite: 169]
- [cite_start]**Neutral - Medium Text:** `#475569` (For secondary text and subtitles) [cite: 170]
- [cite_start]**Neutral - White:** `#FFFFFF` (For backgrounds and inverted text) [cite: 172]
- [cite_start]**AI Message Background:** `#F3F4FF` (A unique, subtle color for AI messages) [cite: 58]

### 2.2 Typography
- [cite_start]**Font:** System Default, Sans-Serif [cite: 174]
- [cite_start]**Headlines (h1, h2, h3):** `font-bold` [cite: 175]
- [cite_start]**Body Text (p):** `text-lg` [cite: 178]

### 2.3 Buttons
- **Primary Button:** Solid Primary Blue background, white text. [cite_start]`bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-md shadow-sm hover:bg-blue-500` [cite: 180]

## 3.0 Page-Specific Component Blueprints

### 3.1 Authentication Pages (`Login`, `Register`)
- [cite_start]**Principle:** Simplicity and clarity are paramount[cite: 4, 13].
- **Layout:** Standard single-column form layout.
- **Components:** Must use the global button and typography styles defined above.

### 3.2 Dashboard Page
- [cite_start]**Principle:** Information must be clean and scannable[cite: 15].
- [cite_start]**Layout:** Must be implemented as a "Bento Grid" to organize active disagreements, resolved cases, and key actions[cite: 15].
- [cite_start]**Empty State:** Must feature a well-designed empty state if the user has no active or resolved disagreements[cite: 16]. This is a critical part of the initial user experience.

### 3.3 Chat Page
- [cite_start]**Principle:** The design must be minimalist and calm, following a "de-escalation by design" principle[cite: 17, 77].
- **Legal Disclaimer:**
    - [cite_start]**Content:** "Please note: The AI does not provide legally binding advice." [cite: 18]
    - [cite_start]**Implementation:** Must be persistent and non-intrusive[cite: 18].
- **Message Styling ("iMessage" Pattern):**
    - [cite_start]**User's own messages:** Right-aligned, Primary Blue background, white text[cite: 56].
    - [cite_start]**Other participants' messages:** Left-aligned, gray background, black text[cite: 57].
    - [cite_start]**AI messages:** Left-aligned, with a distinct AI avatar/icon and a unique background color (`#F3F4FF`)[cite: 58].